column5: I have a couple of friends that want to go there in Feb. and would like to rent a house, challet, (or good size condo). Just thought I'd check and see if anyone was connected.
Cliff, You can check out my home at http://Roatan1.com and also many other rentals on Roatan at http://roatanpropertymanagement.com  And then there is http://roatanet.com
Roatanguy, welcome to the forum.........we look forward to many reports and fish pics (hehe)
Thanks for the laff Chris, that just struck me as hilarious for some reason
...Gave me a good chuckle as well Lew. Normally I would have just deleted it but I thought I'd make it "joke of the day."  Hopefully you'll get the kind of help you were truly seeking Cliff.

I would like to add that you can contact me with regards to my home and other rental properties.  I only accept payment via Western Union, as I live in South Africa.  http://Roatan1.5.com  http://Roatan1.6.com  http://Roatan1.7.com   (Sorry guys I couldn't resist)
I have some contacts in Honduras. PM me and I will see what I can do for you

I know a guy, who knows a guy, who knows a guy, who knows a columbian guy that drops buy there all the time on his trips up to Miami.  I will send you a PM,  Don't mention PM to the guy though he thinks that means Post Mortem and that gets him edgy.  forrest
I've emailed a friend of mine who lives there. He mentioned a while back that he was working on a rental place that would be available soon. I'm sure it would be pretty nice. I'll let you know.  JF
Thanks for all the laughs guys  and I do appreciate the serious replies I have received and look forward to getting the information.
